        <message_html><![CDATA[<p>${mail_script:hello_associate}</p>
<p>The associate annual application verification process has been created to assure that all associates that request access to our production infrastructure follow the company policies and SOX requirements.</p>
<p>When reviewing the information please carefully consider the following:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
<li>Is the employee list accurate?</li>
<li>Is the application access listed correct?</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will then be utilized for auditing purposes by Kate Spade &amp; Company and will be repeated annually.</p>
<p>Once you have thoroughly reviewed the information click the link below to make updates and then the&nbsp;<img style="align: baseline;" title="" src="i_icon.PNGx" alt="" align="baseline" border="" hspace="" vspace="" />&nbsp;icon for the associate you wish to update. Once in the record you have the following options:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
<li>Click on the checkbox that notes that a listed employee no longer reports to you</li>
<li>Un-check the application check to remove an&nbsp; application</li>
<li>Accept the information as accurate by clicking &ldquo;Complete&rdquo;</li>
</ul>
<p>Below is a list of your direct reports and the applications they currently have access to.</p>
<p>${mail_script:app_access_ver_notification_script}</p>
<p>If you have any questions related to this communication then please contact the Support Center.</p>
<p>Thank you!</p>]]></message_html>
